Functie¬≠omschrijving Als Data Scientist heb jij een belangrijke rol in het ontwikkelen van inzichtelijke dataoplossingen en informatieproducten. Bij RVO werk je aan diverse (subsidie)regelingen die bijdragen aan de transities op het gebied van energie, landbouw en duurzaamheid. Jij ondersteunt deze regelingen door het bouwen van modellen en het ontwikkelen van informatieproducten. Met jouw expertise zorg je voor heldere inzichten die helpen bij het nemen van datagedreven beslissingen. Ons werk begint meestal met een vraag vanuit de business, de werkvloer van RVO. Soms komt de vraag direct van de opdrachtgever, de politieke beleidsmakers. We analyseren die vraag om goed in beeld te krijgen wat de precieze informatiebehoefte is en waar kansen liggen voor datagedreven antwoorden. De afdeling Data is in 2023 gestart met agile werken. De agile teams werken verspreid over de verschillende vestigingen van RVO, maar komen wekelijks samen in Utrecht, Zwolle of Assen. De agile teams richten zich op een specifiek thema. Zo ontwikkelen we voor landbouw bijvoorbeeld met radardata een methode om mestopslag beter in kaart te brengen. En voor het thema klimaat zetten we AI in om processen effici√´nter te maken. Op dit moment staan we op het punt om de verdere uitrol van de data science-werkplek in de cloud te realiseren. Jij gaat je bezig houden met het: Innoveren en realiseren van informatieproducten en data-oplossingen. Ontwikkelen √©n doorontwikkelen van datatoepassingen. Meedenken over oplossingen en toepassingen voor concrete vragen. Meedraaien in proeftuinen en experimenten om nieuwe dataproducten binnen RVO te introduceren. Onderhouden van contacten met ketenpartners en opdrachtgevers over de inhoud. Functie-eisen Jij bent klantgericht en in staat om door te dringen tot de kern van de vraag van de opdrachtgever. Deze vraag kun jij makkelijk omzetten naar concrete acties en oplossingen. Jij vertaalt analyses naar de ontwikkeling van een product, dat je zelf kunt opzetten. Je werkt op een vanzelfsprekende manier samen met de juiste collega's en ketenpartners, communiceren gaat jou makkelijk af en je bent een natuurlijke netwerker. Daarnaast heb je gevoel voor businessproblematiek en je speelt makkelijk in op de veranderende politieke omstandigheden. Wat wij graag zien op jouw cv: Een diploma op hbo- of wo-niveau. 3 jaar ervaring in data-analyse/data-science. Brede kennis van data-analysetooling en datatoepassingen ten behoeve van integraal datagebruik, waaronder procesmining, classificatie, machine learning en textmining. Kennis hebben van en/of ervaring hebben met Python (en achterliggend Keras/Tensorflow) qua programmeren. Ervaring met het maken van AI modellen. job_description: Direct message the job poster from De Brauw Blackstone Westbroek Niels Huijgen Niels Huijgen Senior Recruitment Advisor bij De Brauw Blackstone Westbroek De Brauw Blackstone Westbroek is looking for a Data Science Assistant. You will be working in a team with other data science assistants. The ideal candidate We are looking for a student who is flexible, stress resistant and able to work both independently and as a member of a team. A background in either law or technical/analytical studies. Excellent English skills. Working meticulously is very important in this position, and therefore having relevant experience is a plus. Big matters, big risks and big arenas require multidisciplinary, diverse and multinational teams composed of strong strategic thinkers willing to go the extra mile. Cooperation, team spirit and respect for each other's capabilities are highly valued.

Your job In this position, you will be part of our diverse Engineering team that works on our main application. The Insights team is responsible for providing performance data to our customers, which allows them to make data-driven decisions about their product portfolio. As a Software Development team, we are responsible for our Python backend, working closely with external APIs such as Google, Amazon and Bol as well as integrating with internal APIs. The Insights team regularly builds new user-facing features, for which they collaborate with Front-end Engineers and the Product Management team. The team is also working closely together with our Infrastructure and DevOps teams, which are developing many other services that power Channable under the hood, and all together we build our powerful tool! Your challenges Design, develop, and test new product features. Work with external APIs (Google, Amazon, Bol). Collaborate with other team members on breaking features into smaller tasks. Review other team members‚Äô PRs. Improve the reliability and robustness of our application. Work on scalability and performance improvements. Work together with Product Managers on requirements and issues. Collaborate with the Integrations department regarding technical matters. Monitoring the correctness and effectiveness of our systems, and fixing bugs. We use the following technologies and tools: Languages: Python(3.12), SQL. Libraries: Pydantic, typing, requests, logging, Flask, pytest. Tools: Postgres, Alembic, mypy, pip, Sentry, Grafana. Who are you? You are an enthusiastic developer and a critical thinker. At Channable we help each other to become better as a team. That's something you believe in as well. Besides the skills you currently have, an eager-to-learn mindset is just as important. Additionally, you have At least 3+ years of professional experience developing applications in Python. Experience with web APIs and related technologies, as we consume external APIs and build our own web APIs. Good understanding of HTTP, TLS/SSL and TCP/IP. Familiarity with SQL and relational databases, as we use Postgres heavily. Good working knowledge of Linux, git and the command-line. High engineering standards: do you like to leave your code cleaner than you found it? So do we! You have a valid work permit for the Netherlands or EU citizenship. You live in (or close to) Utrecht or are willing to move. You are available for at least 32 hours a week. And then some things are ‚Äúnice to have‚Äù Familiarity with functional programming and its concepts. Having worked with distributed systems before. DevOps mentality: we believe that software teams should be able to complete the software development cycle themselves, and enable them to bring their code to production themselves, and to do so every day. Who are we? Channable was founded in 2014 in the heart of Utrecht. We are now a strong team of +250 diverse individuals, and more than +40 nationalities. Joining Channable means you‚Äôre looking for a bit more than just a job. Diverse as we are, we all share our love for growth, to help, to take ownership, and create an awesome journey together. Feel free to take a further look at who we are here and on our Instagram or Linkedin! Wanna get to know us even more? Give our Culture Playbook a read. What do we do? Channable is a fast-growing B2B SaaS platform that offers a fully integrated way to market your products online. We empower marketers and online businesses to manage, scale, and optimize their marketing. Do you want to read more about our engineering culture? Then have a look at our popular tech blog: https://tech.channable.com Additionally, you can also take a look at some of our open-source work at https://github.com/channable to get a feeling of how we work together and what our code looks like. What do we offer? Gross monthly salary ranging from ‚Ç¨ 4.554 to ‚Ç¨ 6.912 based on a 40-hour work week. The salary is determined based on your experience. 8% holiday allowance - 8% of your yearly salary, which is paid together with your May salary. Annual L&D budget of ‚Ç¨1000 to spend on anything you want to learn. You can take full advantage of this to grow professionally. Saving for old age - we have a saving scheme for old age which can accrue up to 5% of your monthly salary. Company-wide performance bonus, up to 10% of your annual salary, determined yearly by our founders based on financial planning and targets. Traveling to our office? No problem, we got you covered (NS Business Card, or ‚Ç¨0,23 per km if you decide to use a different means of transport). To work in a beautiful historic and fully renovated office in the heart of Utrecht & with a flexible hybrid working policy of (minimum 2 days in the office). Since you can work from home for 3 days a week, we will provide home office supplies. Having flexible working hours means starting your day between 8.00‚Äì10.00 am. 26 vacation days + 2 reload days based on 40 hours. We offer a 3-week-long workcation; and an additional 3 weeks, if you live as an expat in the Netherlands! Are you going to become a parent? We think it is important that you spend time with your newborn. Enjoy 5 weeks of 100% paid partner leave. We want you to feel good - please feel free to use our discounted Urban Sport Club subscription. You have free & anonymous access to the OpenUp platform, and psychologists. This free service is also available to your family members. Channaweekend (we will go abroad in 2025 for a long weekend with all the colleagues from all over the world). At Channable, our Chef and Commis Chef prepare fresh meals Monday to Thursday, catering to all dietary needs - including vegan, vegetarian, and gluten-free - to keep our team fueled and inspired! Additional working conditions like massages, in-office bar (Channabar), parties, sports teams (even personal training sessions at our Channagym), video games, and many more! How can you apply? Are you interested? Please apply by clicking on the "apply now" button below. Please send your application in English. If it's a match, Ioana (Tech Talent Acquisition Partner) will get in touch with you for an introduction call. After that, you'll be invited for interviews. We look forward to hearing from you as soon as possible! Contact by job agencies and recruiters will not be appreciated. Each recruiter or headhunter who approaches us agrees with a donation of ‚Ç¨250 for Make-A-Wish. At Channable, we strive to create and foster an environment of belonging and collaboration and we believe in diverse and inclusive teams.

Wat ga je doen? Menzis heeft als doel om data gedreven te acteren en alle keuzes te maken op basis van data. Het slim analyseren en gebruiken van data speelt daarin een cruciale rol. Mede om deze reden gaan we AI centraler binnen Menzis organiseren en een AI team opzetten. Binnen dit team zul je AI gerelateerde usecases oppakken met een grote waarde voor Menzis of de samenleving. Voor dit nieuwe team zijn wij opzoek naar gedreven en ervaren enthousiastelingen die dit nieuwe initiatief tot een succes kunnen maken. Voel jij je aangesproken, en pas je binnen het profiel, dan gaan we graag met jou in gesprek. Menzis heeft een dataplatform in de Azure Cloud met de meest nieuwe technologie√´n. Jij als Machine Learning engineer binnen dit nieuwe AI team ben je verantwoordelijk voor de industrialisering van Machine Learning modellen in productieomgevingen. Dit omvat het monitoren van modelprestaties, het beheren van modelversies en het optimaliseren van de infrastructuur voor machine learning. Jouw werkzaamheden bestaan onder andere uit: Ontwerpen, ontwikkelen en implementeren van machine learning modellen en algoritmen. Analyseren van grote datasets om waardevolle inzichten te verkrijgen. Transformeren van data naar een bruikbaar formaat. Samenwerken met data scientists en data engineers om ge√Øntegreerde oplossingen te cre√´ren. Optimaliseren van bestaande modellen voor betere prestaties en schaalbaarheid. Op de hoogte blijven van de nieuwste ontwikkelingen en trends in machine learning en AI. Werken in een Agile team met DevOps verantwoordelijkheid. Wat breng je mee? Dat je voor de functie van (senior) Data Engineer over een ijzersterk analytisch vermogen beschikt, is duidelijk. job_title: Data Scientist AI/ML in Product Development (ENG)
job_description: Requisition Number: 23584BR Description Are you a data scientist with a passion for AI and machine learning? Do you want to work on groundbreaking projects that shape the future of environmental management and data engineering? At Stantec in the Netherlands, you'll have the opportunity to use your skills for innovative solutions that make a real impact on the world around us. All from a sustainability perspective to improve our living environment, accelerate the energy transition, and reduce societal costs. At Stantec, we combine cutting-edge technologies with in-depth knowledge of environmental management to fully relieve our clients. With the Soil Risk Map, we quickly, affordably, and pragmatically provide advice on underground risks such as soil contamination, groundwater, unexploded ordnances, ecological and archaeological values. And that's just the beginning. We have ambitious plans to let AI/ML play a central part in our big data product landscape. As a Data Scientist, you are the driving force behind designing, developing, and implementing AI and machine learning models. You work on improving our products using advanced algorithms and big data technologies, such as Azure Databricks and Azure Data Factory. Our goal? Enable self-service data access, apply both predictive and generative AI and ensure the business can make faster and better decisions. At Stantec, you have the freedom to experiment and work with the latest technologies. You design and build CI/CD-based ETL pipelines within our Azure Landing Zones and closely collaborate with the business to translate their needs into data solutions they can independently manage and use. With your passion for AI/ML and automation, you are a pioneer in creating pipelines that not only integrate and transform data but also open the door to innovation and autonomy for our users. The multicultural team you'll be joining combines expertise in (geo) data engineering, software development, automated testing, UI/UX design, and environmental management. As a dev team, we meet at least once a week at the Delft office for planning, retro, and refinement. A joint lunch outing is more the rule than the exception. We also periodically visit our other locations in the Netherlands. Our way of working is scrum infused with agile principles. We primarily focus on developing and delivering long-term solutions that solve problems for an entire industry or market. Currently, we're focused on accelerating the energy transition, automated ETL processes, and smarter data analyses using the latest techniques. We see this way of working as a perfect fit to maintain and increase engagement with customers, the organization, and team members. As a team, we set clear goals and results, giving the development team the freedom to decide how best to achieve them. What will you be doing? Develop and implement AI and Machine Learning models, including supervised and unsupervised learning algorithms, to enhance the Stantec Soil Risk Map and other product initiatives. Utilize big data technologies such as Hadoop, Spark, and NoSQL databases to manage and analyze large datasets. Collaborate with a scrum team to achieve project goals and meet OKRs, employing agile methodologies and continuous integration/continuous deployment (CI/CD) practices. Serve as the sole expert on AI/ML within the team, demonstrating a high level of self-reliance and autonomy in decision-making. Educate and mentor other developers on AI/ML concepts and techniques, including neural networks, deep learning, and natural language processing (NLP). Communicate complex AI/ML concepts to stakeholders in simple and understandable terms, ensuring alignment with business objectives and technical feasibility. What Are We Offering Projects that truly impact people and society. A meaningful career with learning and development opportunities. A good salary, a year-end bonus, and a personal choice budget. 28 vacation days, with the possibility to buy or sell leave days. Working from home arrangement with a monthly internet allowance. Flexible working with various green mobility options. Qualifications Proven experience in AI and Machine Learning, with expertise in algorithms such as regression, classification, clustering, and reinforcement learning. Strong background in big data technologies, including experience with data preprocessing, feature engineering, and model evaluation. Proficiency in programming languages such as Python and SQL, as well as frameworks like TensorFlow, PyTorch, and Scikit-learn. A good command of the English language in both spoken and written forms. Proficiency in Dutch is valued. It is not mandatory, but a plus when you have experience in / knowledge of version control tools (GIT is preferred), geographic information systems (GIS), and tools like FME, ArcGIS en QGIS. Additionally, we are looking for someone who does not hesitate to test hypotheses without knowing the outcomes, enjoys proactively sharing ideas, and gets energized by working in a team. About Stantec At Stantec, you are given the freedom and trust to work in your own way. Sustainability is our priority in both our operations and projects. We support sustainable initiatives worldwide and integrate them into the market and for our clients. Our culture is centered around connection and collaboration, with a genuine commitment to inclusion, diversity, and equality. Sustainability is part of our DNA, and we work on projects that truly impact people and society. Additional Information Apply now! Help build our DEV-team and become a shaper of sustainable change. Send your CV and motivation letter to hr.continentaleurope@stantec.com. Do you have any questions about this vacancy? Contact our Product owner: Christiaan Jolly Tel: 06-22775689 Mail: christiaan.jolly@stantec.com For more information about Stantec; www.stantec.com/nl/werkenbij An assessment may be part of the procedure. Applications can be submitted until 1st May 2025. Work Location(s): Netherlands - Oosterhout, Netherlands-Arnhem, Netherlands-Breda, Netherlands-Delft Employment Type: Full-Time or Part-Time Job Type: Regular Job Category: Environmental Engineer, Technical Advisor

job_title: Senior Machine Learning Engineer - Applied AI
job_description: About The Team The Applied AI team collaborates with product teams across Uber to deliver innovative AI solutions for core business problems. We work closely with engineering, product and data science teams to understand core business problems and the potential for AI solutions, then deliver those AI solutions end-to-end. Key areas of expertise include Computer Vision, ML Optimization, Geospatial AI, Personalization and Generative AI. The ML Optimization team within Applied AI is building new experiences to surface earnings opportunities on the Uber platform, particularly for new earners. We are looking for a strong Machine Learning Engineer to join our team in Amsterdam! About The Role Our team engages with partners across teams to design, develop and productionize machine learning systems for highly complex and vaguely defined problems. What You'll Do Collaborate with product teams to analyze key business problems and develop innovative ML solutions. Collaborate with data science and engineering teams to integrate and validate ML solutions end-to-end. Deliver enduring value in the form of software and model artifacts. Basic Qualifications Master or PhD or equivalent experience in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics or a related field and 2 years of Software Engineering work experience, or 5 years Software Engineering work experience. Experience in programming with a language such as Python, C, C++, Java , or Go . Experience with ML packages such as Tensorflow , PyTorch , JAX , and Scikit-Learn . Experience with SQL and database systems such as Hive , Kafka , and Cassandra. Experience in the development, training, productionization and monitoring of ML solutions at scale. PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in modern deep learning architectures and probabilistic models. Experience in modern generative AI, such as transformer architectures, diffusion models and prompting.

This is Adyen Adyen provides payments, data, and financial products in a single solution for customers like Meta, Uber, H&M, and Microsoft - making us the financial technology platform of choice. At Adyen, everything we do is engineered for ambition. For our teams, we create an environment with opportunities for our people to succeed, backed by the culture and support to ensure they are enabled to truly own their careers. We are motivated individuals who tackle unique technical challenges at scale and solve them as a team. Together, we deliver innovative and ethical solutions that help businesses achieve their ambitions faster. Senior Machine Learning Scientist Adyen is looking for a Senior Machine Learning Scientist to join our team in Amsterdam, a person sitting at the cornerstone of algorithms, mathematics, and engineering, who can solve problems by designing and implementing production-ready machine learning solutions. You will be responsible for building, developing and deploying algorithms that power data products at Adyen. In This Role, You Will Research, design, implement, train, deploy and monitor machine learning algorithms, either for batch prediction or real-time. Examples are-on-line learning algorithms to pick the best optimization decision in a changing environment, clustering algorithms to group customers/shoppers, supervised and semi-supervised learning methods for inference on risk patterns or graph analysis, representation learning for behavior prediction and monitoring, Anti-Money Laundering (AML) systems and real-time anomaly detection based on time-series modeling; Develop orchestrated pipelines for analytical purposes and machine learning training; Contribute to ongoing automation efforts for our experiments, training runs, validation runs and monitoring before, during and after deployment. Furthermore, collaborate with MLOps to improve our machine learning tooling; Create and iterate on state of the art machine learning algorithms with both merchant and product audiences; Stay up-to-date with the latest research and developments in the machine learning field, and apply this where applicable. Who You Are You have 8+ years of experience as a machine learning or data scientist; You have experience with the full machine learning model lifecycle in production flows; You have experience with building and deploying Deep Learning models; You have experience leveraging a big data framework to create the pipelines needed to feed the models with appropriate data; You have a good understanding of software engineering practices as well as data engineering and MLOps principles; You have knowledge of data science and statistics and machine learning techniques. These include a strong grounding in statistical inference, machine learning for prediction, and causal inference. Experience with Deep Learning is a must have.; You have strong familiarity with the standard data science toolkit, such as (py)spark, (Trino) SQL, Tensorflow, PyTorch, XGBoost/LightGBM, Pandas, MLFlow or similar MLOps frameworks, and Airflow; You have an experimental mindset with a launch fast and iterate mentality. Extensive experience with designing and running experiments is essential; You proactively take the lead in projects, from ideation to deployment. You have experience working with a wide range of stakeholders and can clearly communicate complex outcomes over a wide range of audiences. Our Diversity, Equity and Inclusion commitments Our unique approach is a product of our diverse perspectives. This diversity of backgrounds and cultures is essential in helping us maintain our momentum. Our business and technical challenges are unique, and we need as many different voices as possible to join us in solving them - voices like yours. No matter who you are or where you‚Äôre from, we welcome you to be your true self at Adyen. Studies show that women and members of underrepresented communities apply for jobs only if they meet 100% of the qualifications. Does this sound like you? If so, Adyen encourages you to reconsider and apply. We look forward to your application! What‚Äôs next? Ensuring a smooth and enjoyable candidate experience is critical for us. We aim to get back to you regarding your application within 5 business days. Our interview process tends to take about 4 weeks to complete, but may fluctuate depending on the role. Learn more about our hiring process here. Don‚Äôt be afraid to let us know if you need more flexibility. This role is based out of our Amsterdam office. We are an office-first company and value in-person collaboration; we do not offer remote-only roles.

job_title: Junior Researcher on Generative AI Use and Computational Social Science
job_description: University of Amsterdam provided pay range This range is provided by University of Amsterdam. Your actual pay will be based on your skills and experience ‚Äî talk with your recruiter to learn more. Base pay range ‚Ç¨3,378.00/mo - ‚Ç¨5,090.00/mo Are you interested in supporting research on the generative AI use-and-trust dynamics, using advanced citizen science and computational methods, and contributing to the societal discussion on the topic? We are looking for a junior researcher to support ongoing work on the topic, including existing and new research on artificial intelligence such as conversational generative AI agents (e.g., ChatGPT), data donation and computational social science. Generative AI use and Computational Social Science In this position, you will help manage the day-to-day aspects of ongoing research programmes on (a) Trust in the Digital Society, (b) the development and application of citizen science methods to enable individuals to donate their digital trace data to researchers and (c) launch a new multi-year project investigating how individuals use and calibrate their trust in conversational generative AI (e.g., ChatGPT). What are you going to do You will be responsible for: Conducting literature reviews and managing reference software; Conducting pre-registration and analyses of (longitudinal) survey and digital trace (conversational) data; Supporting the development and piloting of citizen science research methods (including data donation), and the analysis of such data; Visualizing data trends for reporting; Collaborating on scientific papers on this topic following the principles of open science; What do you have to offer You: Research Master‚Äôs degree in Communication Science or related field; Advanced quantitative skills, particularly comfortable with automated content analysis (including usage of LLMs for research) as well as survey data analysis (including longitudinal panel data); Demonstrated experience working with R and/or Python; Affinity with the topic of artificial intelligence; and the opportunities and challenges of the digital society; and computational methods; Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal; Ability and interest in supporting all aspects of the research process, including but not limited to literature review; data analysis; concept writing; stimuli development; data collection etc. Experience with the practice of open science; Independent, 'making things work' mentality; Excellent command of English; Dutch language skills a plus If the vacancy appeals to you, but you are doubting whether you might be THE person we are looking for, please do apply. We encourage all qualified applicants, including minorities, women, people with disabilities, and members of other groups underrepresented in academia to apply. We are committed to creating an environment of mutual respect, inclusiveness, equal opportunities with room for situated experiences, diverse perspectives, and ideas to flourish. This commitment applies to our research, organisation, room for flexibility, training, and community activities as well as our hiring strategy. What we offer you The position concerns temporary employment for 0.6 FTE. It is available immediately and lasts for a period of one year. There may be a possibility, after the first year, to extend to a second year pending financial circumstances The UvA offers excellent possibilities for further professional development and education. What Else Do We Offer The opportunity to conduct cutting-edge research in an inspiring academic and international working environment in the heart of Amsterdam An enthusiastic and warm team that is open to new colleagues A position in which initiative and input are highly valued Your application & contact If you recognize yourself in this profile and are interested in the role, we look forward to receiving your application. You can apply via the red button until 25 April 2025. For questions about the vacancy, you can contact: Prof. dr. Theo Araujo, [email protected] Applications in .pdf should include: a curriculum vitae; a short letter of motivation a list of courses followed in your research master‚Äôs a copy of your research master‚Äôs thesis Please include all materials in one single file (PDF).
